---
description: Graphify usage policy for this project
alwaysApply: true
---

This project has a local Graphify graph in `graphify-out/`.

## Default behavior

- Treat Graphify as first-pass context for architecture/discovery tasks, then verify conclusions in source files.
- Use Graphify for:
  - cross-module flow tracing
  - dependency/ripple-impact analysis
  - finding likely hotspots before deep reads
- Do not rely on Graphify alone for line-level correctness; confirm with file reads/tests before final claims.

## Automatic maintenance

- If `graphify-out/graph.json` is missing, run `graphify update .` before Graphify-backed analysis.
- After meaningful code edits in this repo, run `graphify update .` once before final reporting.
- Respect `.graphifyignore`; keep Graphify output out of scope (do not index `graphify-out/`).

## Performance guardrail

- If Graphify retrieval is noisy or low-yield for a task, fall back to direct code search/read without user prompting.
- Use Graphify benchmark results as guidance:
  - strong: >10x token reduction -> keep Graphify-first for architecture tasks
  - weak: <=3x token reduction -> use Graphify only for narrow relationship/path queries

## Optional artifacts

- If `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` exists, consult it for community/god-node orientation.
- If `graphify-out/wiki/index.md` exists, prefer it for quick navigation before deep file reads.
